        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>Our spectral resolution is equivalent to about half the expected widths of individual lines. However since our goal is not to resolve the lines, but to make a detection of the molecules based on summing emission across a group of lines, higher resolution is not required.</prj:justificationText>
            <prj:justificationKey>ED_CORRELATOR</prj:justificationKey>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>Titan subtends an angular size of ~0.75 arcsec at a distance of 9.5 AU (typical), including both the solid body (2575 km radius) and effective increase in radius due to the atmosphere at mm wavelengths (780 km). We conservatively set a largest angular scale of 1.0 arcsec to allow for changes in target distance and request an angular resolution of 0.70 arcsec.</prj:justificationText>
            <prj:justificationKey>ED_ANGULAR_RESOLUTION</prj:justificationKey>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>We chose a bandwidth 468.750 Mhz to cover a spectral interval where each molecule has a band head region about 35 MHz in width. Some continuum is required around each band region for modeling and calibration. The continuum flux is approximately 1.4 Jy, allowing a noise floor of 1.4 mJy given the dynamic range of ALMA band 6 (1000:1). Expected peak line-continuum fluxes range from 1.5 to 20.0 mJy (for gas abundances 0.1 to 1.0 ppb), allowing detections at S/N 1 to 10. After integrating across the band width the effective S/N increases to 4 to 40.</prj:justificationText>
            <prj:justificationKey>ED_SENSITIVITY</prj:justificationKey>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>We require a data rate of 12.2 MB/s, in slight excess of the policy value of 12 MB/s, to allow for us to acquire sufficient continuum spectrum in each window surrounding the broad line multiplets, for calibration and context.</prj:justificationText>
            <prj:justificationKey>ED_HIGH_DATA_RATE</prj:justificationKey>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
    </prj:ScienceGoal>
